  "english": [
    "<b>the sanctification of the day,</b> i.e., <i>kiddush</i> at night, at the beginning of Shabbat, <b>because the sanctification of the day takes precedence over the honor of the day and the honor of the night. And if it is so,</b> that one who fails to recite <i>kiddush</i> at night may do so at any time during the day, <b>let him leave over</b> the cup of wine <b>until the following day and use it for two</b> mitzvot, as he can recite <i>kiddush</i> during the day and simultaneously honor the Shabbat day by drinking wine. Rav Naḥman bar Yitzḥak <b>said to him: A mitzva is beloved in its</b> proper <b>time.</b>",
    "Ravina objected to this answer: <b>And do we say</b> that <b>a mitzva is beloved in its</b> proper <b>time? But wasn’t</b> it <b>taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: <b>One who enters his home at the conclusion of Shabbat recites the blessing over the wine, and</b> then <b>over the light, and</b> then <b>over the spices, and recites <i>havdala</i> thereafter over the cup</b> of wine. <b>And if he has only one cup</b> of wine, <b>he leaves it for after</b> he eats his <b>food,</b> and uses it for Grace after Meals, <b>and arranges all of the</b> other blessings together <b>thereafter.</b> This <i>baraita</i> indicates that <b>we do not say</b> that <b>a mitzva is beloved in its</b> proper <b>time,</b> as one does not have to recite <i>havdala</i> immediately, i.e., before partaking of his meal.",
    "<b>He said to him: I am neither a scholar, nor a speculator, nor</b> an important <b>individual; rather, I teach and</b> systematically <b>arrange</b> <i>halakhic</i> rulings, <b>and</b> the scholars <b>instruct</b> the students <b>in the study hall in accordance with my</b> opinion. I maintain that <b>there is a difference for us between the arrival of the day</b> of Shabbat <b>and the departure of the day.</b> With regard to <b>the arrival of the day, the sooner we</b> welcome the day by reciting <i>kiddush</i> <b>the better, and we</b> thereby express how <b>beloved it is</b> to us. With regard to <b>the conclusion of the day, we delay it so that</b> Shabbat will not appear <b>to be like a burden to us.</b>",
    "The Gemara points out that one may <b>learn from this <i>baraita</i> eight</b> <i>halakhot</i>. The Gemara elaborates: <b>Learn from it</b> that <b>one who recites <i>havdala</i> in the</b> evening <b>prayer must</b> also <b>recite <i>havdala</i> over a cup.</b> The <i>baraita</i> states that one who comes home must recite the blessing over wine and <i>havdala</i>, despite the fact that he has presumably already recited <i>havdala</i> in the evening prayer service.",
    "<b>And learn from it</b> that one who recites the <b>blessing</b> of Grace after Meals <b>requires a cup</b> of wine. <b>And learn from it</b> that <b>a cup of blessing requires</b> a minimum <b>measure,</b> for otherwise it would have been possible for one who has only one cup of wine to simply divide it into two, recite <i>havdala</i> immediately, and still have a cup of wine left over for Grace after Meals.",
    "<b>And learn from it</b> that <b>one who recites a blessing must taste</b> the food over which he recites the blessing. Otherwise, one who has only one cup of wine would be able to use it for both <i>havdala</i> and Grace after Meals. <b>And learn from it</b> that once <b>he has tasted</b> the wine in the cup he has <b>disqualified it</b> from further use as a cup of blessing. <b>And learn from it</b> that even if one has <b>tasted</b> food after Shabbat, he nevertheless <b>recites <i>havdala</i>.</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>קִידּוּשׁ הַיּוֹם, מִפְּנֵי שֶׁקִּידּוּשׁ הַיּוֹם קוֹדֵם לִכְבוֹד",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "יוֹם (וּכְבוֹד לַיְלָה). וְאִם אִיתָא — לִישְׁבְּקֵיהּ עַד",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לִמְחַר, וְלֶיעְבֵּיד בֵּיהּ תַּרְתֵּי! אֲמַר לֵיהּ: חֲבִיבָה מִצְוָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בִּשְׁעָתָהּ. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּמִי אָמְרִינַן חֲבִיבָה מִצְוָה בִּשְׁעָתָהּ?",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְהָא תַּנְיָא: הַנִּכְנָס לְבֵיתוֹ בְּמוֹצָאֵי שַׁבָּת מְבָרֵךְ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עַל הַיַּיִן וְעַל הַמָּאוֹר וְעַל הַבְּשָׂמִים, וְאַחַר כָּךְ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אוֹמֵר הַבְדָּלָה עַל הַכּוֹס. וְאִם אֵין לוֹ אֶלָּא כּוֹס אֶחָד —",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מַנִּיחוֹ עַד לְאַחַר הַמָּזוֹן וּמְשַׁלְשְׁלָן כּוּלָּן",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְאַחֲרָיו, וְלָא אָמְרִינַן חֲבִיבָה מִצְוָה בִּשְׁעָתָהּ! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֲמַר",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לֵיהּ: אֲנָא לָא חַכִּימָאָה אֲנָא, וְלָא חוֹזָאָה אֲנָא,",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְלָא יְחִידָאָה אֲנָא, אֶלָּא גַּמְרָנָא וְסַדְרָנָא אֲנָא, וְכֵן",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מוֹרִין בְּבֵי מִדְרְשָׁא כְּווֹתִי. שָׁאנֵי לַן בֵּין",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עַיּוֹלֵי יוֹמָא לְאַפּוֹקֵי יוֹמָא: עַיּוֹלֵי יוֹמָא — כׇּל",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "כַּמָּה דְּמַקְדְּמִינַן לֵיהּ עֲדִיף, וּמְחַבְּבִינַן לֵיהּ.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אַפּוֹקֵי יוֹמָא — מְאַחֲרִינַן לֵיהּ, כִּי הֵיכִי דְּלָא",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לֶיהֱוֵי עֲלַן כְּטוּנָא. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>שְׁמַע מִינַּהּ מִיהָא מַתְנִיתָא תַּמְנֵי. שְׁמַע",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִינַּהּ: הַמַּבְדִּיל בִּתְפִלָּה — צָרִיךְ שֶׁיַּבְדִּיל עַל",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הַכּוֹס. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: בְּרָכָה טְעוּנָה כּוֹס. וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: כּוֹס",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁל בְּרָכָה צָרִיךְ שִׁיעוּר. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: הַמְבָרֵךְ צָרִיךְ",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁיִּטְעוֹם. וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: טְעָמוֹ — פְּגָמוֹ. וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: טָעַם מַבְדִּיל.",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>וְלָא אָמְרִינַן חֲבִיבָה מִצְוָה בִּשְׁעָתָהּ</b> דלא מבדיל מקמי סעודתא דהוי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שעת הבדלה: <b>לָא <span class=\"dh-divergent\">חכימא</span> אֲנָא</b> דלא אמינא ליה אנא מדעתאי להא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דחביבה מצוה בשעתה: <b>וְלָא חוֹזָאָה אֲנָא</b> מגיד: ולא אמינא ליה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "משמיה דגברא יחידאה: <b>אֶלָּא גַּמְרָנָא אֲנָא</b> כך שמעתי בישיבה:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:4",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>וְסַדְרָנָא אֲנָא</b> מסדר שמועות לפני",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:5",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "רבותי תמיד: <b>עַיּוֹלֵי יוֹמָא.</b> מחבבינא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:6",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ליה ועבדינן קידוש מאורתא כי היכי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:6",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דלנקטיה עילוון הייא: <b>אַפּוֹקֵי יוֹמָא</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:7",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כגון אבדלתא: <b>מְאַחֲרִינַן לֵיהּ.</b> היכא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:8",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דאין לו אלא כוס אחד עד לאחר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:3:8",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "המזון: <b>שְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: הַמַּבְדִּיל בִּתְפִלָּה</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">כו&#x27;</span>.</b> דקתני הנכנס לביתו במוצאי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שבת מבדיל אף על גב דסתם בני",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אדם מבדילין בתפלה: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">וש&quot;מ</span> בְּרָכָה</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>טְעוּנָה כּוֹס</b> ברכת המזון: <b>ושמע</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>מִינַּהּ.</b> (ברכת המזון) [כוס] של ברכ'",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "צריך שיעור דאי לא צריך שיעור",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:5:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ליחלקיה לתרי: <b>וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ: צָרִיךְ</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>הַמְבָרֵךְ שֶׁיִּטְעוֹם</b> דאי לא טעים ליה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ליבריך עליה תרי זימני: <b>וּשְׁמַע מִינַּהּ</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Pesachim 105b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>טְעָמוֹ פְּגָמוֹ.</b> כבר מברכת",
